From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v21 - force ps4_bridge init at attach time

After v20 (skip DP link training for Liverpool/Gladius) the clock
recovery error was gone but ps4_bridge_pre_enable / ps4_bridge_enable
still never fired.  Root cause: PS4 GPU uses DCE v8 with LEGACY drm
encoder helpers (.prepare/.commit, no atomic_enable).  The DRM bridge
chain pre_enable/enable callbacks are only invoked from the atomic
modeset path's drm_atomic_bridge_chain_pre_enable / _enable helpers,
which dce_v8_0_encoder_commit doesn't call.

So even though ps4_bridge_attach succeeds and ps4_bridge_get_modes
runs, the actual HDMI bridge chip (MN864729/MN86471A) is never
programmed -- it stays in whatever state the BIOS left it.  No DP
sync, no HDMI output.

Workaround: force-call ps4_bridge_pre_enable + ps4_bridge_enable from
ps4_bridge_register, right after drm_bridge_attach.  Hardcode mode to
CEA VIC 16 (1920x1080 @ 60Hz) since we don't have an EDID-driven mode
yet at attach time.

If v21 works:
- Monitor lights up at 1920x1080@60Hz
- fbcon visible during boot

If v21 doesn't work:
- ps4_bridge ICC writes might still fail (cq_exec error)
- Or the bridge needs the encoder to be programmed first (the GPU's
  DP transmitter), in which case we need v22 to invoke bridge from
  dce_v8_0_encoder_commit instead.

This is a workaround.  The proper fix is to migrate dce_v8_0 to the
atomic modeset framework, but that's a much larger project.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
@@ -786,5 +786,18 @@
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
 
+	/* v21: amdgpu's dce_v8_0 uses LEGACY drm encoder helpers
+	 * (.prepare/.commit) — the bridge chain pre_enable/enable callbacks
+	 * are NEVER invoked from that path on PS4.  Force-program the bridge
+	 * here at attach time with a hardcoded 1080p60 VIC so the
+	 * MN864729/MN86471A converter is set up regardless of how amdgpu
+	 * drives the modeset later.  Without this, bridge_pre_enable +
+	 * bridge_enable never fire and HDMI output stays dark. */
+	mn_bridge->mode = 16;	/* CEA VIC 16 = 1920x1080 @ 60Hz */
+	pr_info("ps4_bridge: forcing bridge init at attach (mode=VIC %d)\n",
+		mn_bridge->mode);
+	ps4_bridge_pre_enable(&mn_bridge->bridge);
+	ps4_bridge_enable(&mn_bridge->bridge);
+
 	return 0;
 }
